Lin,<br><br>
It is a sad testimony for humanity and a disturbing comparison to our previous great history that we can see our country in this way.<br><br>
I worry about our future because so many have lost the resolve to sacrifice for those things we hold so dear.  If we continue we will find that the leadership we look to in the time of crisis will chose to debate the finer ideological concepts while the less civilized enemy pillage at will.<br><br>
Become a student of history.  You will likely find disturbing parallels.  Hope we do not repeat the cycle of the rise and fall of great nations.<br><br>
I agree we have all sacrificed and we must find that middle ground.  No group can carry the weight alone.<br>

